global%20trust%20in%20non-proliferation%20frameworks.%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20occasional%20challenges%20and%20regional%20complexities%2C%20the%20NPT%20remains%20a%20key%20pillar%20in%20the%20effort%20to%20balance%20national%20energy%20development%20with%20global%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20nuclear%20policy%2C%20India%20has%20always%20taken%20a%20firm%2C%20independent%20path.%20While%20191%20countries%20around%20the%20world%20have%20signed%20the%20Treaty%20on%20the%20Non-Proliferation%20of%20Nuclear%20Weapons%20(NPT)%2C%20India%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20that%20has%20consistently%20refused.%20But%20why%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20lies%20in%20fairness%2C%20global%20power%20structures%2C%20and%20regional%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20core%20issue%3A%20An%20unequal%20treaty%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20primary%20objection%20to%20the%20NPT%20is%20that%20it%20creates%20two%20classes%20of%20nations%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20%E2%80%9Cnuclear%20haves%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20the%20five%20countries%20allowed%20to%20possess%20nuclear%20weapons%3A%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Russia%2C%20China%2C%20France%2C%20and%20the%20United%20Kingdom.%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20%E2%80%9Cnuclear%20have-nots%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20all%20other%20signatory%20countries%2C%20which%20are%20permanently%20banned%20from%20developing%20nuclear%20weapons.%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20India%E2%80%99s%20perspective%2C%20this%20is%20not%20a%20balanced%20global%20agreement%E2%80%94it%E2%80%99s%20a%20system%20that%20locks%20in%20the%20power%20of%20a%20select%20few%20while%20denying%20the%20same%20rights%20to%20others.%20India%20believes%20that%20if%20global%20disarmament%20is%20the%20true%20goal%2C%20then%20all%20nuclear%20states%20should%20eventually%20be%20expected%20to%20denuclearise%E2%80%94not%20just%20those%20who%20weren%E2%80%99t%20%E2%80%9Cgrandfathered%E2%80%9D%20into%20the%20treaty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20simple%20terms%3A%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CWhy%20should%20some%20countries%20be%20allowed%20to%20keep%20their%20nuclear%20weapons%20forever%20while%20others%20are%20permanently%20forbidden%20from%20having%20them%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20This%20has%20been%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20position%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20regional%20reality%3A%20Security%20concerns%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20refusal%20to%20sign%20the%20NPT%20isn%E2%80%99t%20just%20about%20fairness%E2%80%94it%E2%80%99s%20also%20about%20practical%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EChina%20became%20a%20nuclear%20power%20in%201964%2C%20well%20before%20the%20NPT%20was%20signed.%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPakistan%20developed%20nuclear%20weapons%20outside%20the%20NPT%20framework%2C%20intensifying%20security%20tensions%20in%20South%20Asia.%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20India%2C%20signing%20the%20NPT%20would%20have%20meant%20giving%20up%20its%20right%20to%20develop%20nuclear%20weapons%20in%20a%20region%20where%20two%20of%20its%20neighbours%20already%20had%20them.%3Cbr%3EGiven%20these%20realities%2C%20India%20decided%20to%20maintain%20its%20strategic%20flexibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20philosophy%3A%20No%20first%20use%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20India%20is%20not%20a%20part%20of%20the%20NPT%2C%20it%20has%20always%20emphasised%20responsibility%20and%20restraint.%3Cbr%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20doctrine%20is%20built%20around%20the%20%E2%80%98No%20First%20Use%E2%80%99%20policy%2C%20which%20means%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIndia%20will%20never%20use%20nuclear%20weapons%20unless%20it%20is%20attacked%20first%20by%20nuclear%20weapons.%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIts%20nuclear%20arsenal%20is%20purely%20a%20deterrent%2C%20not%20a%20weapon%20of%20aggression.%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20principle%20reflects%20India%E2%80%99s%20broader%20vision%3A%20nuclear%20weapons%20should%20only%20exist%20to%20prevent%20war%2C%20not%20to%20fight%20one.%20India%20also%20supports%20the%20long-term%20goal%20of%20a%20nuclear-weapon-free%20world%2C%20but%20it%20insists%20that%20disarmament%20must%20be%20fair%20and%20universal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhy%20this%20matters%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20decision%20not%20to%20sign%20the%20NPT%20isn%E2%80%99t%20about%20defiance%E2%80%94it%E2%80%99s%20about%20seeking%20an%20agreement%20that%20respects%20equal%20rights%20and%20real-world%20security%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20India%20remains%20outside%20the%20treaty%2C%20it%20has%20continued%20to%20advocate%20for%20responsible%20nuclear%20behaviour%20and%20has%20built%20international%20trust%20through%20agreements%20like%20the%20Civil%20Nuclear%20Deal%20with%20the%20United%20States%20in%202008%2C%20which%20recognised%20India%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20program%20without%20NPT%20membership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20bigger%20picture%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20stand%20highlights%20the%20complex%20balance%20between%20global%20ideals%20and%20regional%20realities%2C%20and%20the%20ongoing%20challenge%20of%20creating%20fair%20frameworks%20in%20international%20diplomacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Leila%20Badyari%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1750679636000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2Fisrael-iran-war-1750675802.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D454167%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Nuclear%20Non-Proliferation%20Treaty%20(NPT)%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20widely%20accepted%20global%20agreements%20%E2%80%94%20but%20